LABORATORY
Reviewed outside colonoscopy pathology.  See chest x-ray and lab data.
#1 Colon cancer at the rectosigmoid junction
Mr. Burns presents for surgical management of colon cancer described at 16 cm from the anal verge.  We discussed location issues with regard to colorectal cancer, and I have requested colorectal surgery consultation for this afternoon with consideration of flexible sigmoidoscopy and tattooing to confirm the location.  Patient is interested in laparoscopic surgery, and his only prior abdominal surgery was appendectomy in the 1940s.  His CT and chest x-ray will be sent to Radiology for interpretation.  Lab work, ECG, and Colorectal Surgery consultations are pending.
We discussed the role for adjunctive treatment if this is colon cancer as well as neoadjuvant treatment if this is felt more consistent with a rectal cancer on flexible sigmoidoscopy.
#2 Preoperative medical evaluation
Lab work and ECG are pending.  Once these are obtained and satisfactory, patient is okay for anesthesia.  Lakeview Family Practice Radiology reviewed his outside chest x-ray.  Please see HPI for other PAME details.
Discussed with Paul Walling, note to follow.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

